  <diagram name="2. Phase 1b final architecture" id="p2-page">
    <mxGraphModel dx="2476" dy="1226" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="0" pageScale="1" pageWidth="2200" pageHeight="1400" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="p2-0" />
        <mxCell id="p2-1" parent="p2-0" />
        <mxCell id="p2-t" parent="p2-1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=28;fontStyle=1;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#2E7D32;" value="Phase 1b rev-5 final — deployed &amp; E2E-validated (2026-04-21)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="1700" x="50" y="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2-ts" parent="p2-1" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=14;fontFamily=Helvetica;fontColor=#555555;" value="Two submission paths forked at POST /v1/tasks by `execution_mode` field. INTERACTIVE (`bgagent run`, or `submit --watch`): Lambda writes TaskTable + `task_created` event, SKIPS orchestrator, returns 201. CLI then opens SSE direct to Runtime-JWT; server.py hydrates params from TaskTable by task_id, runs pipeline SAME-PROCESS in the SSE microVM. ORCHESTRATOR (plain `bgagent submit`, default): Lambda writes TaskTable + async-invokes OrchestratorFn → Runtime-IAM (SigV4, Accept: application/json, sync spawn). CLI `watch --transport auto` reads `execution_mode` from GET /tasks/{id} and polls for orchestrator tasks (no cross-runtime live attach). Defence-in-depth: if a client tries SSE against a non-interactive task, server returns 409 RUN_ELSEWHERE (wrapped as 424 by AgentCore). E2E-A: bgagent run → PR #11 in 54s. E2E-B: submit + watch --transport auto → snapshot sees execution_mode=orchestrator → polls → DDB." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="2000" x="50" y="70" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="p2-bar" parent="p2-1" style="line;strokeWidth=2;strokeColor=#2E7D32;html=1;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="10" width="2100" x="50" y="110" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
